He lost his father in the Tsunami and became a PMC to take care of his bedridden mother. He might be hot-headed and a braggart but he's also a decent man.
After being orphaned, this former CIA special operative has been training tirelessly to cope with her loss. She hides under the cover of a well-heeled Sheikh's trophy wife.
Her older brother was murdered in a terror attack. He was also her teammate. Since the tragedy, she's been tracking the ones responsible for the attack. She excels in intense operations.
This former KSK officer is a legend among his peers due to his combat skills and for his unique origin: he is a clone. White Victor is the product of the soldier cloning project led by the military.
Stray bullets in a gang fight killed his parents. He grew up surrounded by wars. Turning any object into a weapon is certainly a fine art that he learnt on the streets.
Former member of the French Police special-response unit, GIGN. Born in a poor neighborhood, young Jean trained his parkour abilities running through the intricate maze of streets.
She lived in a PMC camp after losing her family in a terror attack. She might be petite and nimble-looking, but she proves among the deadliest with a machine gun in hands.
He entered the army, following his father. He made significant contributions, having a mind of steel and showing initiative. He became a PMC to protect the weak, a rather surprising idea.

He was born in a Mafia family, whose father was the boss. He decided to join the armed forces in order to escape this dark side he grew up in. After getting through tough training and combat, he won the much harder battle with crime syndicates.
He is a steadfast sniper whose extraordinary skills unnerve the enemy. He also happens to be an Olympic medalist.
Civilian life was unbearable after being discharged, so he joined a PMC. He's an expert at securing a foothold.
He used to be a smuggler in Afghanistan but was attacked by a group of terrorists. After the incident, he decided to become a PMC to escape the weak side.
Former MI6 agent famous for wiping out the HQ of one of the fiercest terrorist groups using his tactical expertise.
He used to be a wolf hunter in Siberia. He decided to hunt PMCs who destroyed his home land alone. He was later hired by Red Bullet once he built a reputation.
An undefeated master of martial arts. It seems he and his old friends have an old on-going feud with an unknown group.

A private ICBM launch complex that was abandoned when the energy supply was cut off. NAF took over the facility and renovated it, using Trinitium as a power source. EDEN has now sent PMCs in to shut it down.

The NAF decided to substitute its missiles' radio-inertial guidance system for a GPS guidance system using a control facility in South America. Naturally, EDEN took exception to this and conflict ensued.

A top EDEN engineer on route to a secret assignment was stranded on a construction site when the helicopter transporting him suffered a malfunction and crashed. The NAF sent its forces to seize the sensitive data he carried, while EDEN sent its own PMCs to protect him and the aforementioned data.

The NAF's absolutist doctrine was not well received by some segments of the population. A resistance movement sprung up to oppose it, but the government's brutal repression drove it underground. Taking note of this, EDEN started supporting the movement with funds and weapons.

The NAF's Black Sea Fleet is blockading EDEN's main Russian port. Intelligence sources confirmed illegal Trinitium transactions taking place there and as a response, the NAF sends its PMCs to seize the port.

A strategic steel factory funded by the West located in the Caucasus region in Georgia. EDEN took control of the facility when the Western nations' control was loosened after the Tsunami. NAF is now sending its forces to take back control of the factory.

An island somewhere off the northwest coast of Africa. OC Industries, long rumored to be connected to the Mafia, had a secret robotics laboratory here before the Tsunami. Both NAF and EDEN found it however, and quietly sent their PMCs to take control of it.

He was dissatisfied with the NAF's taxation policy and decided to take action. He attempted to take action by forming a consortium to support EDEN and oppose the NAF. The usual suspects took notice and sent in their PMCs.

HK416 chambered with 7.62x51mm NATO, the bigger caliber being meant to obtain a sniper rifle. Used in semi-sniping.
Korean army's service weapon K2 with a shortened barrel. Attached retractable stock, practical for Run and Gun.

Israeli bullpup rifle developed to replace its heavy Galil predecessor. Due to its short aiming axis, it is mostly used with an optical sight.
A Polish assault rifle designed as a modular rifle system. Configurations include a modified caliber or a bullpup configuration.
An improved version of the M4 made for the US Army's Special Forces. Rails were added on four sides of the barrel cover so that various accessories can be attached, depending on mission needs.
An Italian assault rifle integral to the Future Soldier Program. Most parts of the weapon are covered with reinforced plastic.
Modular A3 version of the Austrian AUG bullpup rifle with a Picatinny Rail included. The modular design allows easy adaptation to tactical situation.
Former Soviet Union service assault rifle. Its famed high reliability allows it to be operated under any environmental conditions. It's the most popular gun worldwide.
An assault rifle derived from the FN FAL. Its high stopping power generates a strong recoil, limiting it to short burst fire. Weight is reduced by using aluminum.
Heavy version of the SCAR, using 7.62x51mm rounds. Made for long range combat in wide open areas.
Rifle designed for marksmen of the American Navy SEAL teams. Its short barrel is compensated by aiming attachments.
SMG with AR-15 type upper receiver designed to use the 5.7x28mm P90 magazine. 50 rounds capacity.
Russian assault rifle. Its first two shots are fired at high rate, reducing initial recoil.
Training M4 similar to the M4-ACC-M, but without rails to attach further elements.
A machine pistol designed for counter-terrorism units. The contracting breechblock and the retractable stock makes it easy to carry. It also can have a unique forward grip.
SMG using 4.6x30mm lightweight rounds. Used by KSK, DEVGRU, and other special forces. Saw action in famous desert operations.
A Belgian SMG that uses a special 5.7x28mm rounds. Modified version with a rail, a 50 rounds magazine can be attached on top of the barrel.
A medium-sized Russian SMG using 9x19mm Parabellum rounds. Characterized by using a helical magazine.
This modified version of the MP5 has been the choice weapon for SAS, SWAT, and other Special Forces all around the world for a long time. This SMG is suitable for counter-terrorism operations.
Despite its rather short effective range, it is the fastest firing SMG. The unique movement of the breechblock and low position of the barrel allows superior recoil control.
Advanced SMG that uses 25 round UMP magazine. Characterized by the use of a delayed blowback system with .45 ACP pistol rounds.
Russian SMG designed as a counterpart to the personal defense weapons of the West. Easy and simple to manipulate and carry.
A Personal Defense Rifle firing 5.56mm rifle rounds. Bullpup configuration is perfect for escort missions.
American Sniper Rifle firing 12.7mm rounds and 12x magnification scope used for long range sniping.
A German bolt-action sniper rifle with high accuracy. Designed as a bullpup, the attached bipod improves precision.
German semi-automatic sniper rifle designed for counterterrorism and urban warfare. Although suitable for precise shooting, it is heavier and has a shorter effective range than other sniper rifles.
A semi-automatic sniper rifle made by the USSR. First rifle designed for precision shooting, sporting a 4x magnification PSO-1 as standard scope.
A rifle supplied to the Soviet army as service weapon during World War II. Characterized its long silhouette, it was the primary weapon of the Eastern European Bloc for a long time.
A German precision rifle designed for hunting. The reloading mechanism is meant for fast operation.
An improved version of the M249, being itself an improvement of the M60 following Vietnam war. For continuous supply, an ammunition pouch is attached to it.
A lightweight squad automatic weapon made in Singapore. Includes a 100 rounds magazine. It only weights 5kg.
Improved version of the MG42, the service machinegun of the German army during WWII. Heavy, the bipod is used for defensive and covering fire.

An improved version of the beloved M1911, a large caliber semi-automatic pistol. Although it has a limited magazine, it packs superior stopping power.
A large caliber Italian semi-automatic pistol designed for police forces. Smooth design aims to reduce the aggressive feeling of a weapon.
Revolver with a long 8-inch barrel. Double action trigger, and although it uses .357 magnum rounds, it is accurate.
Israeli semi-automatic pistol using Magnum rounds. Heavy weight and strong recoil are compensated by the revolver-grade destructive power.
American shotgun with a bullpup design. Shoots 12 Gauge shells and can fire up to 240 rounds per minute.
Italian shotgun that can switch between semi-automatic and pump-action. Each shell has to be loaded separately due to the cylindrical magazine design.
Standalone German grenade launcher. Since it uses a side swing mechanism, it does not have to be put up during reloading.
Compound crossbow with a sight. It is possible to shoot without making much noise, and the bolts can be retrieved and used again.
American machine pistol using Vector's Super V technology. The unique recoil system allows rapid continuous fire and stable recoil control.
Knife with the traditional curvy shape of the Sulawesi region of Southeastern Asia. Improved as a single-edged blade, using reversed grip style.
Launcher made to fire anti-drone electromagnetic pulse shells at long range. It can precisely aim at the target by using the Lock-On feature.
A small combat axe that's easy to carry. A masterpiece by Townsend, a company highly regarded for its bladed weapons.
A drone shaped marker mine. When triggered, it sticks to the enemy and sends real-time location for a certain period of time.
A gas canister round for riot control. Uses CS gas. When exposed, causes tears, pain, and suffocation.
A robot emitting fake shooting sounds to confuse the enemy. A more realistic effect is attained by continuous movement combined with the drone's AI.
Explosive device moving forward when thrown. Can climb up walls; explodes upon encountering enemies or after a certain period of time.

Grenade that can stick to the enemy or the terrain. An explosion that close to target provides a great killing power.
A multi-role explosive device that can be remotely triggered after attaching to a surface at the right timing. It is miniaturized to improve concealment.
An S-Mine springing up, exploding at torso level. Although it has a high killing power, damage can be reduced by lying prone.
Anti-personnel mine shooting metal balls in a fan pattern. Uses a laser sensor to detect approaching enemy and detonate.
A throwing knife, made light and thin for aerodynamics. Can be quickly thrown and be reused upon retrieval.

Non-lethal grenade emitting a powerful shockwave. Target will experience blurry sight, disorientation, and slowed movement speed.
Non-lethal grenade diffusing an extremely thick smoke. Lasts for some time around the throwing point.
A grenade designed to set fires. The flammable substance generates high heat to start flames to burn the surroundings.
An anti-drone electromagnetic pulse grenade. By using plastic explosive in its structure, it can explode after attaching to the target. Greatly damages drones.
Tactical Knife with a small explosive device. To make it easier to throw, a spear-type blade has been used. It explodes a second after landing on a target.
